result.execSummary:
The defendant Timothy John Eaton was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Timothy John Eaton is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Timothy John Eaton was found guilty of Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: 3:09 Defendant Timothy John Eaton in court with attorney Christopher R. Bub.  Sean Edward Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Froelich: guilty to Ct#2; dismiss Ct#1 and Ct#3. 1 year probation: written letter of apology to the victim and to be given to agent or Victim Witness Coordinator. No contact L.R.P (08-12-01 DOB), court costs. Atty Bub and Def agree; Atty Bub is free to argue sentencing.  Plea Questionnaire and Waiver of Rights form is filed with the court; court reviews with Def.  Constitutional rights explained to defendant.  Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights. Def pleas guilty to Ct#2; Bub stipulates to a factual basis.   COURT ACCEPTS PLEA, FINDS DEF FREELY, INTELLIGENTLY, KNOWINGLY & UNDERSTANDINGLY MADE AND WAIVES CONSTITUTIONAL RIGHTS. Court finds and adjudicates Def guilty of Ct#2. Dismissed Ct#1 and Ct#3. Atty Froelich requests probation sentence. Atty Bub gives argument for sentencing; requests fine without probation. Froelich objects. Court: Def to write a heart felt meaningful apology to victim and submit to Atty Bub or to the DA's office within 30 days. Imposes a fine in the amount of $515 including the DNA surcharge. NO contact with L.R.P (dob 04-12-2001). 6 months to pay fine. Appeal rights are given to the defendant.

4:02  Defendant Timothy John Eaton in court with attorney Christopher R. Bub.  Defendant Timothy John Eaton in custody.  Sean Edward Froelich appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Defendant has copy of complaint   Defendant waives reading of the complaint    Constitutional rights explained to defendant  Exam'd re: understanding of law, penalty and rights  DEF PLEADS NOT GUILTY to each count.  Court reviews the bond conditions with the defendant  Pre-trial conference scheduled for November 16, 2015 at 04:30 pm.
